Testing RSA Beta1 Build version 20060813_1601

Problem: When you try to set the Binding for a NewPort to an Existing Binding, when the 'Specity Binding wizard appears, select nothing and press Ok, NPE and Unhandled event loop exception message are in the log file.

Steps to reporduce:

1.    Launch the RSX application
2.    Create a General Project  and then add a file to the project. Call the file MY.wsdl
3    .Add a Service to the  Design diagram
4.    The right click on the NewPort in the NewService and select 'Set Binding->Existing Binding...'
5    When the Wizard for 'Specify Binding' appears, there are no listings in the Components. This is good because we did not add any.
6   Select the option "Working Set" at the bottom of the Wizard and you will get a NullPointerException in the log and a Unhandled Event loop.
